  <name>W01 Tue - FTP Test + VO2max Assessment</name>
  <description>• STRUCTURE: 30 min warmup → 5 min all-out → 10 min recovery → 20 min max effort → 15 min easy → 5 min all-out → 10 min easy → 3x3 min @ 110-115% FTP (3 min easy between) → 15 min cooldown. • Comprehensive testing. FTP test (20-min × 0.95). Then 5-min max for power profile. Finally, VO2max repeatability test (can you hold power across 3 intervals?). This reveals limiters: If 5-min power &amp;lt;120% FTP = VO2max limiter. If power drops &amp;gt;5% on VO2 intervals = VO2max repeatability limiter. If everything tests strong but you fade in long races = durability limiter. Write everything down.

• UNBOUND GRAVEL 200 - HYDRATION:
&gt;90 min high intensity/intervals/heat: 90g carbs/hr. 1.5 bottles/hr minimum. 1000-1500 mg sodium/hr. Aggressive cooling: ice sock, dump water, shade stops when practical. Replace ~75% of losses within 2 hours post-ride.

• UNBOUND GRAVEL 200 - DAILY BASELINE HYDRATION:
Start day hydrated: ~500 ml water + 500-1000 mg sodium with breakfast. Pre-ride (60 min before): 500 ml fluid + 300-600 mg sodium. Aim for light urine color (not clear).</description>
